snippet.textDisplay:
DEATH … seems to be the only time LIFE actually matters, or is celebrated by the living. But all the tears in the living don't come close to that of the dead, because after DEATH, comes JUDGEMENT.

The NBA doesn't exist up there, nor is wealth or popularity anything to Him. There is only ONE THING that will matter when eternity comes, and if you haven't "checked THAT box" and done what He expects you to do, then … "bitter weeping and gnashing of teeth" indeed!

"The dead know nothing." - King Solomon

Solomon is right. No one other than God is 'looking down'. Kobe knows NOTHING about what ya'll are saying or doing, NOR is he thinking about it because the fact is, if he is in Paradise (made his Salvation sure before he died), he is in so much bliss and joy, seeing things that his eyes and mind have never seen or thought of, he is in too much bliss to even think about anything on the earth. But, if he is in Hades, all that cativates him is the sheer horror and deep fear of knowing what comes after Judgment. He ALREADY knows. He has enough background in the Truth of God's Word to no exactly what the end result of his Judgment is.

In Heaven, the NBA doesn't exist, nor does earthly fame, nor does earthly riches, nor does popularity. We are ALL truly EQUAL before God and NO ONE is your master or subordinate, boss or employee. We are ALL naked and ashamed. There is only ONE THING that matters - did or didn't you repent of sin and obey God to the end of your life. If the answer is 'no' … then the result is 'woe!' But if the answer is 'yes' … then the result is 'bless.'



"Let the dead go and bury their dead. YOU continue to follow Me" - Jesus

Harsh realities. But as the same time, "Jesus wept" … because He loved Lazarus. And as one who has baried 9 frieds before the age of 30, not to mention family members, I'm well aquainted to this pain, and I know REAL emotion when I see it, and fake "sniffles" too. People who FEEL the deepest tend to be the last ones to TALK about it, cause we can't 'talk' about it because it still hurts too much to talk about it. Facts. I know the pain well. Grieve if you must, but if you forget the whole reason you were born … there is coming a day that you will wish you were never born at all.

snippet.textDisplay: I know there is always a lot of talk in basketball about "who is the GOAT", and "who is the top 5 best of all time". Growing up basketball has always been my favorite sport to play, but i never watched basketball until i was 19 (2017-2018 season). But i did watch kobe highlights. Once i started watching highlights of all the greats over the past couple years, watched documentaries and off-court interviews, no one is like KOBE to me. He has always been my #1. He has always been the mvp of all sports to me. Every shot i've took at a trash can, or lob behind my back for an impossible shot, ive said "KOBE". The people who say Kobe isn't top 5 instantly go in my head as disrespectful. Kobe's life was so centered around basketball, he is basketball to me. Kobe, thank you so much for what you did for basketball. Thank you so much for your mentality and work ethic. Thank you so much Kobe, you will always be my #1
